		"description": "<p>At 1st level, you learn a battle hymn, which&nbsp;can be expressed in any type of&nbsp;performance. Once at the start of your turn,&nbsp;you can activate a battle hymn by&nbsp;expending one use of your Bardic&nbsp;Inspiration (no action is required).&nbsp;Performing a battle hymn requires your&nbsp;concentration, as though you were casting a&nbsp;spell. Once activated, a battle hymn&nbsp;continues until you lose concentration or the&nbsp;start of your next turn.</p>\n<p>The number of battle hymns you know are&nbsp;listed in the Battle Hymns Known column of&nbsp;the Bard table. Whenever you gain a bard&nbsp;level, you may choose one battle hymn you&nbsp;know and replace it with a new battle hymn.&nbsp;Your bard level determines what battle&nbsp;hymns you can learn.</p>\n<p><strong>Audience. </strong>Unless otherwise noted, a&nbsp;battle hymn does not have a target until&nbsp;you choose one, and each hymn targets a&nbsp;single creature within 30 feet. You can&nbsp;choose to target a creature at any time,&nbsp;but once you have chosen a target of your&nbsp;battle hymn, the hymn&rsquo;s target can&rsquo;t be&nbsp;changed.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Sustained Song. </strong>When you have an activated battle hymn but have not chosen a creature to benefit from it yet, at the start of your turn when it would end you can instead choose to sustain the battle&nbsp;hymn until the start of your next turn&nbsp;without expending a use of Bardic&nbsp;Inspiration.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 256.156px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 46.5116%;\"><col style=\"width: 53.4884%;\"></colgroup>\n<thead>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">Bard Level</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">Battle Hymn</td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">1st-4th</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.kl7koxuwp6edgi9y]{Battle Hymn: Harmony of Pain}</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.99b04hvh44uuv8av]{Battle Hymn: Overbearing Rhythm}</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.am5r25ebgscf2273]{Battle Hymn: Song of Clarity}</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">5th-8th</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.6prqen2qfzmnpbxg]{Battle Hymn: Bastions of Justice}</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.w809qy93c5f33t2x]{Battle Hymn: Call to Arms}</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.fjy7opusafsr55r1]{Battle Hymn: Placid Tones}</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">9th-12th</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.vim6c3olnci1dubs]{Battle Hymn: Heaven's Blessing}</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.dcl4v0rzoyyif9pw]{Battle Hymn: Ode of Blood}</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.okn7tljq4n6nu8d3]{Battle Hymn: Willful Serenade}</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">13th-16th</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.re62ukwtzxreo6i0]{Battle Hymn: Doomsayer}</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.zfb00h3gr85gramz]{Battle Hymn: Onward to Battle}</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.lzwwsy22m9xg67ie]{Battle Hymn: Rise and Fight}</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">17th-20th</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.79ivma6eqd6hx1p2]{Battle Hymn: Bring Low the Foe}</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.30slt39sv4beeyt9]{Battle Hymn: Carry the Spirit}</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.09bf780zdri2i8cf]{Battle Hymn: Inspiring Crescendo}</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
